<dl id="n20231b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n20" href="#n20231b">N20 (VI.B.13)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n20all.htm#n20231b"> 231(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Blake &amp; Dragone / <font face="wake">T</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The well-known story of Blake and the Dragoon. Blake was enraged to find a Dragoon called Schofield in his garden. Without waiting to find how he had got there (he had been invited by the gardener), Blake angrily drove him out. The Dragoon brought false charges against Blake of speaking seditiously against the King and Blake was brought to trial. He was acquitted but took revenge by use of Schofield&apos;s name in <cite>Jerusalem</cite> and <cite>Milton</cite>.]</font> <small> Darrell Figgis, <a name="DFPW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DFPW"><cite title="source">The Paintings of William Blake</cite></a> (1925) 57-8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
